OL,6,FIn an apology to Parliament Mr Sunak
OL,7,Fsaid...
OL,9,F"I want to make wholehearted and
OL,10,Funequivocal apology for this terrible
OL,11,Finjustice.JThis is a day of shame for
OL,12,Fthe British state. Today's report
OL,13,Fshows a decades-long moral failure at
OL,14,Fthe heart of our national life, from
OL,15,Fthe National Health Service to the
OL,16,FCivil Service, to ministers in
OL,17,Fsuccessive Governments, at every level
OL,18,Fthat people and institutions in which
OL,19,Fwe place our trust failed in the most
OL,20,Fharrowing and devastating way."
